<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/681> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #681" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.22.3; Diod. 16.53.1; Chr. 354 (Petico V et Penno II); Fast. Hyd. (Roetico et Poeno); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 105, 404f. Sulpicius held command against Tarquinii which was granted a forty year truce, Quinctius against Falerii (Liv. 7.22.4-5). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 6." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/667> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #667" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.19.6, both patricians; Diod. 16.46.1; Chr. 354 (Petico IIII et Publicula II); Cassiod.; Degrassi 105, 404f. Sulpicius commanded against Tarquinii and Valerius against the Volscians (Liv. 7.19.8-9). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 37, no. 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/663> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #663" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "After long delay two patrician Consuls were elected (Liv. 7.17.10-12, and 18.1). Servilius and M. Fabius were appointed twice (Liv.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/662> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #662" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.17.13 (two patrician Consuls), and 18.1; Diod. 16.37.1; Chr. 354 (Petico III et Publicola); Fast. Hyd. (Potito [sic] et Publicola), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Sulpicius held command against Tarquinii, and Valerius against Tibur (Liv. 7.18.2). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 37, no. 8. See Degrassi 105, 404f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/649> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #649" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.12.9. Won an important victory over Gauls who had reached Praeneste and Pedum, and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 7.12.9-15.8; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; Frontin. Str. 2.4.5; App. Celt. 1; Eutrop. 2.5.2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 28; Oros. 3.6.2; Degrassi 34f., 105, 402f.). See 361, Trib. Mil., on Manlius Torquatus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/648> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #648" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Sulpicius' name, see Act. Tr." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/632> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #632" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.9.1; Diod. 16.6.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -St]olo; S.'s name entire); Chr. 354 (Stolo et Uetico); Fast. Hyd. (Stollone et Petino), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 105, 400f. The Consuls made war on the Hernici (Liv. 7.9.1-2); one of them, probably Sulpicius, celebrated a triumph (Act. Tr., [-Ma]rt.; Degrassi 68f., 540)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/629> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #629" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Rallied the forces of Genucius and repulsed a Hernican attack (Liv. 7.7.1-3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/614> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #614" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.2.1; Diod. 15.95.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -] Peticus; Licinius' name entire); Val. Max. 2.4.4; Plut. RQ 107; Chr. 354 (Petico et Calbo); Fast. Hyd. (Petito et Galba), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 32f., 104, 400f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/613> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #613" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Fast. Cap. Calvus was Cos. in 364 and Stolo in 361; in Livy, Val. Max. and Plut. their positions are reversed. On a similar confusion in our sources for the name of Licinius, the Mag. Eq. of 368, see 368, note 2. Sulpicius' praenomen T. in Livy is corrected from Cassiod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/608> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #608" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.; cf. Liv. 7.1.8, on the death of a Censor (Postumius) in 365; Degrassi 32f., 104, 398f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/607> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #607" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Beloch (RG 83) regards this censorship as an interpolation in the Fasti, both because another censorship follows in 363 and the same gentile names appear for the Censors of 380. Münzer (RE s. v. \"Sulpicius\" 29) would accept this one but not the earlier one (see under 380). The persons named in this year can be distinguished from those in 380, and the death of one Censor is attested by Livy in 365. This would itself make another censorship necessary soon thereafter. Cram (HSC Ph 51 [1940] 78ff.) rightly defends both censorships." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/565> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #565" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 6.27.2; Diod. 15.50.1; Fast. Cap. (note 1); Chr. 354 (Publicola V et Mamertino VI); Degrassi 32f., 102, 392f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/564> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #564" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The names are preserved in Fast. Cap. as follows: L. Valerius L. f. [- - - -]; P. (Valerius) L. f. L. [n. Poti]tus Poplicol. III; Connelius, Menenius, and Sulpicius, entire as above; [- - - -]n. Mamercin. VI; Cn. [Sergius - f. - n.] Fiden. Coxo III; Ti. Papiri[us - f. - n.] Crassus; L. (Papirius) [- f. - n.] Mugillanus II. Livy lists six, L. and P. Valerius, C. (sic) Sergius, Licinius (sic) Menenius, P. (sic) Papirius, and Sergius (sic) Cornelius Maluginensis. Diod. indicates eight, and in his confused Mss tradition may be identified two Valerii (of P. the praenomen only), Menenius (with praenomen L.), Sulpicius, Aemilius, Papirius (only one, with praenomen T.), and the apocryphal names {Gr} (add. F), C. or Cn. Terentius, and {Gr} (add. F); Degrassi 393. The nine named in Fast. Cap. have no parallel, and it appears that no college of more than eight was known to Claudius (ILS 212; cf. Liv. 5.2.10; 6.37.6; Dion. Hal. 11.56.3). Clearly Fast. Cap. has the most seriously interpolated tradition." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10228> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10228" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Galleis. MRR I.121, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 57." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10227> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10227" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Herniceis. MRR I.118-9, Itgenshorst p. 263, Rich no. 54." .
